<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Keygen on KevCaz's Website</title><link>https://kevcaz.github.io/tags/keygen/</link><description>Recent content in Keygen on KevCaz's Website</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>Content under CC0 1.0 Universal unless otherwise specified.</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://kevcaz.github.io/tags/keygen/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Generate a ssh key with R</title><link>https://kevcaz.github.io/notes/2020/04/2020-04-04_generate_a_ssh/</link><pubDate>Sat, 04 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kevcaz.github.io/notes/2020/04/2020-04-04_generate_a_ssh/</guid><description>&lt;p>I now frequently use &lt;a href="https://github.com/features/actions">GitHub actions&lt;/a> to
deploy websites on gh-pages. One way to do so requires to use a &lt;a href="https://help.github.com/en/github/authenticating-to-github/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent#generating-a-new-ssh-key">ssh
key&lt;/a>
(the full procedure is well explained, &lt;em>inter alia&lt;/em>, in the README of
&lt;a href="https://github.com/peaceiris/actions-gh-pages">peaceiris/actions-gh-pages&lt;/a>). As
I am used to work with the Terminal, when I need such a key, I use the following
command line:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div style="color:#575279;background-color:#faf4ed;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">
&lt;table style="border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;">&lt;tr>&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#575279;background-color:#faf4ed;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code>&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#575279;background-color:#faf4ed;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ ssh-keygen -t rsa -b &lt;span style="color:#ea9d34">4096&lt;/span> -C &lt;span style="color:#ea9d34">&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#286983">$(&lt;/span>git config user.email&lt;span style="color:#286983">)&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ea9d34">&amp;#34;&lt;/span> -f gh-pages -N &lt;span style="color:#ea9d34">&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>which generates two files:&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>